Taiwan Labor Minister Aims to Raise Minimum Wage Again, CNA Says

-- B y   A d e l a   L i n
-- 
2011-04-21T02:59:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/taiwan-labor-minister-aims-to-raise-minimum-wage-again-cna-says.html
Taiwan’s Council of Labor Affairs’
minister Wang Ju-hsuan aims to raise the minimum monthly wage by
more than 3 percent after a review meeting scheduled in July,
Taipei-based  Central News Agency  reported today.  The  minimum wage  in January was increased 3.47 percent to
NT$17,880, the report said.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
